The '''National NewsMedia Council''' is a national press council that reviews and adjudicates complaints from the public about the news media in [[Canada]].<ref name=G>{{cite news|title=National Newsmedia Council to oversee member publications|url=http://www.theguardian.pe.ca/News/Local/2015-09-16/article-4278207/National-Newsmedia-Council-to-oversee-member-publications/1|accessdate=13 November 2015|work=The Guardian|date=16 September 2015}}</ref> The council was created as an amalgamation of several regional press councils, including the [[Ontario Press Council]].
== History == The National NewsMedia Council was created in 2015.<ref name="G"/> It replaced regional press councils, including the [[Ontario Press Council]], the Atlantic Press Council and the British Columbia Press Council.<ref name="G"/> The council was created after declining financial support for regional press councils.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|title = The launch of the National Newsmedia Council recognizes the reality that news now has no borders.|url = https://www.thestar.com/opinion/public_editor/2015/09/11/new-era-for-media-accountability-in-canada-public-editor.html|newspaper = The Toronto Star|date = 2015-09-11|access-date = 2015-11-13|issn = 0319-0781|first = Kathy|last = English}}</ref> The Quebec Press Council and the Alberta Press Council declined to join.<ref name=":0" /> The National NewsMedia Council was supported at its creation by major newspapers and chains including the [[Toronto Star]], [[the Globe and Mail]], [[Postmedia News|Postmedia]] and [[Sun Media]].<ref name=":0" />
The first president and CEO is [[John Fraser (journalist)|John Fraser]].<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.thestar.com/news/canada/2015/09/09/national-press-council-launched.html|accessdate = 13 November 2015|work = The Canadian Press|publisher = Toronto Star|date = 9 September 2015|title = National press council launched}}</ref> [[Frances Lankin]] is the first chair.<ref>{{Cite news|title = BERTON: Holding journalists to account|url = http://www.thespec.com/opinion-story/5919999-berton-holding-journalists-to-account/|newspaper = The Hamilton Spectator|date = 2015-09-19|access-date = 2015-11-13}}</ref>
