The '''Rusa''' (Rusha) language, also known as '''Arusha-Chini''', is one of the [[Bantu languages|Bantu]] languages of [[Tanzania]] spoken by the [[Chaga people]]. It is spoken in the Chaga area of the [[Kilimanjaro]] region, and forms a [[dialect continuum]] with other [[Chaga languages]].
